<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-06T00:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-06T00:35:00-05:00" n="550" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">761.91/217: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-06T09:00:00+03:25">May 6,
                                        1940—9 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 6—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>101. My 91, April 30,4 p.m.<note n="20" xml:id="d550fn20">Not
                                    printed.</note> It now seems practically certain that the
                                Iranian Government has been obliged to put several flying fields at
                                the disposal of the Soviets. A number of Iranian refugees who were
                                expelled from Russia—see my despatch No. 1294, May 13, 1938<note n="20" xml:id="d550fn21">Not printed.</note>—have just been
                                engaged by the Iranian Air Force presumably to serve as
                                interpreters.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>